<collectingCountry box="[1159,1195,332,358]" name="Philippines" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">PH</collectingCountry>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1195,1207,350,364]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">w</subScript>
= 1.35; P 
<subScript attach="both" box="[1317,1329,350,364]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">w</subScript>
P 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1344,1349,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">l</subScript>
= 1.15; E 
<subScript attach="both" box="[168,173,385,399]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">l</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[190,202,386,400]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">w</subScript>
= 1.7; EH 
<subScript attach="left" box="[319,331,386,400]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">w</subScript>
= 1.8; EP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[443,455,386,400]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">w</subScript>
= 1.34; EP 
<subScript attach="left" box="[581,586,385,399]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">l</subScript>
= 2.7. Body length 
<quantity box="[809,910,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[992,1081,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[272,381,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18A</figureCitation>
). Anterior margin of epistoma straght. Head widest at eye level. Eyes moderately convex, large in dorsal view, circumocular impression wide (
<figureCitation box="[686,792,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of genae angularly rounded. Puncturation of head moderately coarse and sparse, interpuncture distance 1.5–2 times as long as puncture diameter. Head pubescent with sparse, reddish, moderately long, recumbent setae (
<figureCitation box="[890,1027,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18D, E</figureCitation>
). Ventral side of epicranium coarsely and densely punctured by raduliform punctures, gula almost smooth (
<figureCitation box="[920,1020,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Antennae comparatively short, with only two apical antennomeres, extending beyond base of pronotum, reaching 1/6 of elytral length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
Prothorax (
<figureCitation box="[324,496,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18B, D–F</figureCitation>
). Pronotum weakly cordate, widest at middle, weakly transverse (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1337,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of pronotum moderately rounded, slightly emarginated near antero-lateral corners and stronger emarginated near postero-lateral corners; anterior margin slightly rounded at middle and widely emarginated laterally; base weakly bisinuate. Antero-lateral corners projected, acute and pointed at apex; postero-lateral corners straight, pointed at apex. Lateral margins beaded (
<figureCitation box="[626,769,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18D, E</figureCitation>
); anterior margin with interrupted bead at middle. Disc of pronotum evenly strongly convex, not flattened along lateral margin, only lateral sides more gentle. Puncturation of disc fine and sparse, puncture diameter near 3–4 times as short as interpuncture distance in middle and 3 times on lateral sides; punctures round (
<figureCitation box="[534,639,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18D</figureCitation>
). Prosternum with coarse, sparse, short transverse wrinkles and pubescent with long, recumbent, sparse setae (
<figureCitation box="[605,706,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Prothoracic hypomera not flattened along margin, with smooth, weak, sparse wrinkles and distinct sparse granules bearing long seta (
<figureCitation box="[913,1011,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18F</figureCitation>
). Prosternal process shiny, moderately punctured on sides, densely pubescent with subrecumbent reddish setae slightly convex at apex, beaded (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18B, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
Pterothorax (
<figureCitation box="[348,494,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18A, B</figureCitation>
). Scutellar shield triangle, with straight margins, coarsely and densely punctured. Elytra elongate-oval, widest at middle; punctures in striae fine, slightly elongate, widely spaced; punctures in interstriae fine and sparse, with almost the same size than strial ones, but deeper (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1125,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Anterior half of mesoventrite densely pubescent, coarsely and densely wrinkled. Mesepisterna, mesepimera and metepisterna with coarse and dense puncturation and long recumbent setae; intercoxal part of mesoventrite finely and sparsely punctured and sparsely pubescent; metaventrite with moderately coarse and moderately dense punctures, pubescent with long recumbent setae (
<figureCitation box="[348,444,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig.18B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
Legs. Trochanters with brush of short dark-reddish setae and one long seta (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1143,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Basal third of meso- and metafemora without the same brush on flex side (
<figureCitation box="[707,809,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Tibiae straight. Pro- and mesotarsomeres 1–4 strongly widened, trasverse, subequal to width of apex of protibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[326,530,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18B, C, G–J</figureCitation>
). Abdominal ventrites with moderately sparse, fine raduliform puncturation and pubescence of long, recumbent, reddish setae. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[788,955,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figs 18C, G–J</figureCitation>
). Apical part of the basal piece of aedeagus almost smooth, with only pair small areas of fine longitudinal rugosity (
<figureCitation box="[969,1066,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18J</figureCitation>
). Apical piece strongly narrower from base to apex, widely rounded at apex, dorsal surface without median groove or keel (
<figureCitation box="[1163,1258,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1401,186,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[172,1416,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Euboeus zubovi sp. nov., habitus, details of structure.A = male, dorsally; B = male, ventrally; C = male inner sternite VIII, ventrally; D = male, head and pronotum, dorsally; E = ditto, dorso-laterally; F = prothoracic hypomeron; G = spiculum gastrale; H = median lobe of aedeagus, ventrally; I = tegmen, ventrally; J = apical piece of aedeagus, dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6785970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6785970/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Fig. 18J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" box="[199,401,1555,1581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="479" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1591,1617]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named in honour of Andrey Zubov (
<collectingRegion box="[957,1056,1591,1617]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Moscow</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1067,1146,1591,1617]" name="Russia" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Russia</collectingCountry>
), my colleague and excellent insect collector.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="479" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,259,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1663,1689]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species differs from all representatives of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kulzer" authorityYear="1964" box="[1075,1199,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Probaticus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huedepohli">
<emphasis box="[1075,1199,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">huedepohli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the following characters: head pubescent with recumbent setae; pronotum with projected, acute, pointed at apex anterolateral corners; prothoracic hypomera with sparse distinct granules; the apical piece of the aedeagus sub-triangle, strongly narrowed from base to apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
